  <prompt>
    Build composition integration tests per spec FR-52: `/summarize #engagement-letter.docx`
    (command + single reference) AND `/draft response to @opposing-counsel about #motion-to-dismiss`
    (command + multiple references + interleaved text).

    These are integration tests that exercise the full parse → resolve → decorate → send chain
    across tasks 080 (parser), 081 (hard-slash executor — not used here, hard slashes don't compose
    with references), 082 (soft-slash router), 083 (reference resolver). The test verifies the
    BFF chat-endpoint payload includes: (a) correct command intent; (b) all references resolved
    to canonical IDs; (c) intent metadata flows through to CapabilityRouter; (d) the agent
    receives a coherent prompt with all resolved entities.

    No new code surface — just tests. Place under
    `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/__tests__/composition.integration.test.ts`
    or similar per the SpaarkeAi test convention.

    NFR-11 binding: also include a regression test confirming that the same intent expressed in
    natural language ("summarize the engagement letter") still works via the existing
    CapabilityRouter path with no command intent set.

    Frontend-only task; BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend integration-test engineer with familiarity with the SpaarkeAi conversation pane,
    Pillar 8 components (080/081/082/083), and the BFF chat-endpoint payload schema.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Composition test file exists; covers FR-52 examples; verifies parse → resolve → decorate →
    send chain. All tests green. Documents the composition contract for future Pillar 8 extensions.
  </goal>

